OK, this turns them back on, but the TES and AWS Batch ones appear to not actually work when turned on. The TES batch system tests already sometimes fail, but I think usually in a different way, and the AWS Batch batch system failure looks like it could be real too.

@stxue1 I think this broke in https://github.com/DataBiosphere/toil/pull/4646 where the tests were commented out. Do you think you can fix the tests to pass again?

@DailyDreaming Do we want to leave the AWS Batch and (probably) TES batch systems broken in `master`? Or do we have to revert the other PR? Or is this not actually broken somehow?
